## Timeline of the scandal

* Oct 2000: Breathless email from Turner and Sponsel ("Imminent Anthropological Scandal").
* Rapid debunking of the book: UCSB, U Michigan, Susan Lindee, National Academy of Sciences, International Genetic Epidemiology Society, Society for Visual Anthropology, and more...
* Feb 2001: American Anthropological Association (AAA) establishes an investigative "Task Force" whose members have severe conflicts of interest.
* May 2002: AAA accepts Task Force Report finding Neel & Chagnon "guilty" of inappropriate conduct.
* Referendum to rescind the Report: The Task Force violated AAA policies & ignored basic principles of fairness & due process.
* June 2005: <span style="color:red;">AAA Task Force Report **rescinded**. Vote: **846 to 338**.</span>

